00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:53,640
I used to be into younger guys,

3
00:00:55,360 --> 00:00:58,160
but after the Spring Festival,
I've decided to be realistic.

4
00:01:04,680 --> 00:01:07,200
- Here is your dish.
- Thank you.

5
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Say something.

6
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:21,600
You know why I came to find you today?

7
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:22,840
Jiayu has this practice problem here,

8
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:26,040
- and you're going to solve it for me.
- Who told you to say that?

9
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,320
They're over there
trash-talking younger guys.

10
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,240
Nothing to say in defense?

11
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:34,520
Just eat.

12
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,800
I do think women mature

13
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,720
faster than men of the same age.

14
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,760
Younger guys are too playful.

15
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:44,280
They're not really suited
for anything long-term.

16
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:45,720
He said we're immature!

17
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,000
Especially

18
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:49,360
for an independent woman like you, Ms. Ye.

19
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:52,120
I think you should consider
someone mature, maybe a year or two older,

20
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,560
emotionally stable,

21
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:55,560
financially secure, someone who can

22
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,480
truly support you.

23
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,280
Listen, man.

24
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:04,360
This is called youth and vitality.

25
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:07,400
All the cool ladies nowadays
are into younger guys.

26
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,600
Who'd want to date some boring guy
with a poker face, right?

27
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:17,120
I wasn't talking about you!
What I mean is…

28
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,160
He…

29
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,280
He's older doesn't mean
he's emotionally stable!

30
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:23,680
Especially the ones with glasses.
It makes my blood pressure spike!

31
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,200
I… I think…

32
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,320
what Dr. Gao meant was that

33
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,200
compared to younger men,

34
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:32,760
older men might be
better equipped to solve problems.

35
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,840
- Yes.
- It's a personality thing!

36
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:36,800
What does age have to do with it?

37
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:38,400
Younger guys are sincere and passionate.

38
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:40,640
And the older ones? Aside from being
greasy, they're just full of schemes.

39
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:42,360
What else could they possibly offer?

40
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:44,760
Not all older guys are greasy.

41
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:47,000
And plenty of younger guys
are mature and thoughtful too.

42
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:49,120
But younger guys
have less romantic experience.

43
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,400
They simply don't know how to care
for someone else. You have to admit that.

44
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,520
Wait.

45
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:55,360
Having a ton of romantic experience
is something to brag about now?

46
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:58,120
I'm not bragging! I'm just saying
they don't know how to care for people!

47
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,320
We younger guys
can take care of people too!

48
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:02,320
Who said it was about you?

49
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,560
- We were just chatting.
- He's actually pretty interesting.

50
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:05,480
It's nothing, really!

51
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,400
Have something to eat.

52
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,560
Wow, you're pretty quick for an old timer!

53
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,400
Finished talking?

54
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,360
Just a discussion.

55
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,920
I don't think
your discussion was meaningful.

56
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:21,040
A woman like Ms. Ye deserves to be with
someone of equal education and background,

57
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,800
a quality man with good upbringing,

58
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,920
someone who can offer her a real future.

59
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,440
So, you're talking about me?

60
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:32,960
Just because you're highly educated,
you look down on the three of us,

61
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,800
- who only graduated from junior high?
- That's not it.

62
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,240
A degree doesn't mean you're cultured.

63
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,240
Good manners don't mean
you have a good heart.

64
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,160
A good upbringing
doesn't guarantee a future.

65
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,160
- A good future doesn't mean compatibility.
- Enough!

66
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:47,920
Can you stop this now?

67
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,680
Sorry about that.

68
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:56,320
My friend here
has been a bit sensitive lately.

69
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,080
You might have struck a nerve. So…

70
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:01,080
What nerve? I'm not sensitive at all!

71
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,120
Okay! That's enough from both of you.

72
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,400
Stop ganging up on him.

73
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,600
We young boys listen

74
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:09,600
and follow the ladies' words.
You could learn.

75
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,960
- Please, have a seat.
- Okay.

76
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,519
- Sorry about that, Dr. Gao.
- It's all good.

77
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:26,400
Go on. Dig in.

78
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,680
I'm seething.

79
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,400
Please eat! Thanks.

80
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,680
SPICY STEAMED RED SNAPPER, SCALLOPS
